              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb30 comfortaa">To identify fraudulent immigration consultants, follow these steps:</p>
                <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">1. Check for Registration:</span> Ensure the consultant is registered with the College of Immigration and Citizenship Consultants (CICC) or a Canadian provincial or territorial law society, or the Chambre des notaires
                     du Québec for Canada. Similar registrations can also be looked up on Govt. of India websites for authenticity. </p>
                 <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">2. Verify Contact Information:</span> Cross-check the contact details on the consultant's website with their Google search results and verify their physical address.</p>
                 <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">3. Look for a Secure Website:</span>  Ensure the website has a padlock icon in the address bar and starts with "https://".</p> 
                    <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">4. Check for Red Flags:</span>   Be aware of consultants who offer special deals, or have no contact information on their website.</p> 
                    <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">5. Check for Reviews:</span>   Look for reviews and testimonials from previous clients on the consultant's website and social media presence.</p>   
                    <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa"><span class="brand-color uppercaes fw600">6. One-on-One Consultation:</span>    Reputable consultants will offer a one-on-one consultation before offering a contract.</p>   
                <p class="fs18 lineheight33 mb20 comfortaa">Remember, it is your decision to hire a consultant, and doing so will not guarantee special attention or approval of your application.</p>
                </div>
